Last Broadcast Date: Wed 5 Oct 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, we hear about May Shigenobu's childhood on the run as the daughter of two revolutionaries. Also, Jamal Edwards a young media entrepreneur on escaping the violence of his London childhood. And Rob Spence - the Canadian film maker with a video camera in his eye socket. Show less